{"id":"a013","internalId":"82909145-afb7-4bd1-8a38-c940f746225e","createdAt":"2026-01-28T06:53:17.954Z","updatedAt":"2026-03-24T10:39:59.436Z","status":{"code":"PUBLISHED","name":"Published"},"assessmentType":{"code":"CAR_ASSISTED_DRIVING","name":"Car Assisted Driving"},"assessmentDiagrams":[],"publicationDate":"2023-06-07","publicationYear":"2023","ratingYear":2023,"SPRefNumber":"a013","umbracoRefNumber":null,"rescueSheetURL":null,"greenNcapURL":null,"frontalImageURL":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/82909145-afb7-4bd1-8a38-c940f746225e/Alfa-Romeo-Tonale__9ba02b08fc085bc9_original.png","frontalImage":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/82909145-afb7-4bd1-8a38-c940f746225e/Alfa-Romeo-Tonale__9ba02b08fc085bc9_original.png","altText":null,"width":1144,"height":760,"formats":{"large":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/82909145-afb7-4bd1-8a38-c940f746225e/Alfa-Romeo-Tonale__f0b071c824a105bb_lg.webp","width":1144,"height":760},"small":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/82909145-afb7-4bd1-8a38-c940f746225e/Alfa-Romeo-Tonale__b6c2191c61a4b723_sm.webp","width":320,"height":213},"medium":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/82909145-afb7-4bd1-8a38-c940f746225e/Alfa-Romeo-Tonale__2d9108dba452a894_md.webp","width":768,"height":510},"xlarge":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/82909145-afb7-4bd1-8a38-c940f746225e/Alfa-Romeo-Tonale__f0b071c824a105bb_xl.webp","width":1144,"height":760},"thumbnail":{"url":"https://data-cdn.euroncap.com/media/assessment-media/82909145-afb7-4bd1-8a38-c940f746225e/Alfa-Romeo-Tonale__df510707faf0884f_thumb.webp","width":156,"height":104}}},"newsMarketURL":"https://news.euroncap.com/safercars/choose-a-car/kia-ev3---euro-ncap-2025-assisted-driving-results---very-good-grading/s/1d7e1ed3-0757-4654-aec9-efce26e4913b","resultApplicability":"all","comments":"<p>Alfa Romeo’s system name ‘Active Driving Assist’ accurately portrays system functionality. However, the promotional material makes several misleading references to automation. The Tonale does not offer a head-up display showing the system status in the driver’s direct line of sight. Alfa Romeo did not equip the Tonale with an internal camera and the system relies only on steering wheel input for Driver Monitoring. The system balances driver steering input with lane guidance, promoting co-operative driving.</p><p>The Tonale combines map-based speed limit information with real time camera inputs to manage fixed, variable and temporary speed limit signs. The system does not adapt speed for upcoming road features such as corners, junctions or roundabouts. The Tonale responds to avoid a collision in most of the ACC test scenarios and requires AEB interventions in the more critical stopped vehicle, cut-in and cut-out tests. The driver is supported through the S-Bend, staying centred in the lane at all test speeds. The vehicle does not have an Active Blindspot system designed to prevent lane changing into adjacent vehicles. A lane-change assist function is not available. In the case of an unresponsive driver, the maintains steering control and brings the car to a controlled halt. If either the camera or radar is blocked the car provides a timely warning and prevents system activation.</p><p>The Alfa Romeo Tonale provides modest levels of Vehicle Assistance and Driver Engagement but good Safety Back-up resulting in a Moderate but balanced system.</p>","testedHandOfDrive":null,"assessmentTags":[],"assessmentData":{"carAssistedDriving":{"disclaimer":"When using Assisted Driving Systems (also known as SAE Level 2 systems), a driver’s responsibilities include monitoring the system’s control of speed, braking and steering at all times, strict compliance with traffic rules, and maintaining situational awareness throughout the journey. Certain situations might negatively influence the system’s performance (e.g. poor weather, faded lane markings, construction zones, exiting a tunnel), resulting in a sudden interruption of the lateral and/or longitudinal support (system disengagement). Moreover, the system may fail to detect certain road users such as motorcyclists not directly in front of the vehicle, or stationary objects. Appropriate fitness to drive is critical for safe travel, even when using Assisted Driving Systems. Visual distraction (e.g. eyes off the road), impairment (e.g. drowsiness, intoxication) as well as unresponsiveness, poses high risks. It is highly recommended to keep your hands on the steering wheel at all times to ensure immediate reaction when the system disengages.","nicePublicationDate":"June 2023","assistedDrivingPerformance":{"assistanceCompetence":{"score":54,"maxScore":100,"normalisedScore":54,"driverEngagement":{"score":54,"maxScore":100,"normalisedScore":54,"elements":{"consumerInformation":{"score":15,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"YELLOW","elements":{"marketingMaterial":{"url":"https://www.alfaromeo.com/models/tonale?adobe_mc_ref=#modal-safety-popup","viewDate":"15/05/2023"},"quickStartGuide":false,"handbook":{"url":"https://euroncap.blob.core.windows.net/media/77245/alfa-romeo-tonale_vehicle-handbook_driver-assist-systems.pdf"}}},"systemStatus":{"score":14.7,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"YELLOW","elements":{"continuousSystemStatusIndicator":"YELLOW","systemStatusChangeIndicator":"YELLOW"}},"driverMonitoring":{"score":10,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"ORANGE"},"drivingCollaboration":{"score":15,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"YELLOW","elements":{"comment":"System continues to assist while driver steers to avoid obstacle"}}}},"vehicleAssistance":{"score":62,"maxScore":100,"normalisedScore":62,"elements":{"speedAssistance":{"score":10.7,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"ORANGE","elements":{"speedAssistSystems":{"responseToFixedSpeedLimit":"Start slowing down after sign","responseToVariableSpeedLimit":"Start slowing down after sign"}}},"adaptiveCruiseControlPerformance":{"score":21.7,"maxScore":40,"verdict":"YELLOW","elements":{"adaptiveCruiseControlAutoResume":{"systemAssistanceMaintained":"Automatic resume within 5s of stop and driver input required over 5s"}}},"steeringAssistance":{"score":30,"maxScore":35,"verdict":"GREEN","scenarios":{"80km":{"verdict":"GREEN"},"100km":{"verdict":"GREEN"},"120km":{"verdict":"GREEN"}}}}}},"safetyBackup":{"score":76,"normalisedScore":76,"elements":{"systemFailure":{"score":25,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN","scenarios":{"sensorBlockedAtStartup":{"camera":{"engagement":"System can NOT be engaged after a 5 minute drive","warning":"Visual Warning within 5 minutes after sensor blocking"},"radar":{"engagement":"System can NOT be engaged after a 5 minute drive","warning":"Visual Warning within 5 minutes after sensor blocking"}},"sensorBlockedVehicleMovingSystemInactive":{"camera":{"engagement":"System can NOT be engaged after a 5 minute drive","warning":"Visual Warning within 5 minutes after sensor blocking"},"radar":{"engagement":"After a 5 minute drive","warning":"After sensor blocking"}},"sensorBlockedVehicleMovingSystemActive":{"camera":{"engagement":"Within 2 minutes after blocking","warning":"After sensor blocking"},"radar":{"engagement":"After sensor blocking","warning":"After sensor blocking"}}}},"unresponsiveDriverIntervention":{"score":20,"maxScore":25,"verdict":"GREEN"},"collisionAvoidance":{"score":31.8,"maxScore":50,"verdict":"YELLOW"}}}}}},"carSafety":null,"carAssistedDriving":{"assistedDrivingGrading":{"code":"MODERATE","name":"Moderate"},"assistedDrivingPackName":"Active Driving Assist","safetyAssessmentId":"0991","assessmentReviews":[]},"truckSafety":null,"vanSafety":null,"model":{"id":"32b34e7d-d481-458c-8ce8-5c5d3498ef34","createdAt":"2026-01-21T19:15:58.76668+00:00","updatedAt":"2026-01-21T19:15:58.76668+00:00","code":"ALFA_ROMEO_TONALE","name":"Tonale","class":{"code":"SMALL_SUV","name":"Small SUV"},"vehicleType":{"code":"CAR","name":"Car"}},"make":{"id":"b9a71343-681b-4982-8df2-87493c4999db","createdAt":"20